 {"id":"bd-j1r0f","title":"[SPORK][App][Core] Deterministic Start/Stop Ordering Contract (no hidden races)","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-06T05:43:30.327198688Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-06T05:44:28.907427523Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["app","determinism","spork"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j1r0f","depends_on_id":"bd-12qan","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-06T06:36:13Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-j1r0f","depends_on_id":"bd-sd083","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-06T06:36:13Z","created_by":"import"}],"comments":[{"id":284,"issue_id":"bd-j1r0f","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"## Why

Without an explicit ordering contract, "works on my machine" interleavings will bleed into:
- trace fingerprints
- crashpack divergence
- DOWN/EXIT semantics
